{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix uninitialized variable access in PDCP encryption module\n\n### Summary\nThe NR PDCP encryption module accessed uninitialized memory when processing security configuration during UE initial setup. The bug caused intermittent encryption failures and MAC-I verification errors during handover procedures.\n\nThe uninitialized access occurred in the security context setup function where the ciphering algorithm identifier was read before being properly initialized from the security mode command.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_PDCP/nr_pdcp_security.c`: Initialize ciphering algorithm variable before use.\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_PDCP/nr_pdcp_entity.c`: Add validation check for security configuration parameters.\n\n"
}